Profile?language=EN>Zeremus AyonaeRo</A> at: 3/23/02 8:26:13 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uhildeguard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hilde Guard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/23/02 11:09:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2056.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hitsmode setup</span><hr size=1> my suggestion:<br><br>/hitsmode me m4 310 643 10 4 0 0 25<br>/hitsmode my m4 278 643 10 4 0 0 25<br><br>this will bring 2 colums, without background (no flicker), between your chat windows, buttons or whatever you have. find out the correct coordinats for your screen. its looks 10 rows like:<br><br>64      23<br>101    63<br>20      45<br>...      ...<br>...      ...<br><br>but finally i turned off this feature, because my misses still displayed in chat windows and i lost the feeling for output performance :/<br><br>/hitsmode my|me on<br><br>will bring back the old style <p><br><center><img src=http://www.stephanleu.de/hilde-logo2.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utostifenrirsget.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tosti Fenrirsget</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/23/02 11:28:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2056.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Aye, that's th' one I use.</span><hr size=1> This is a set-up fer 1024x768 resolutions.<br><br>Mind ye, mine's a bit mer tidy since I alt-m that menu oot o' the way; move the buffs intae a three-by-five window up a shert distance; et al.<br><br>A bit o' explanation fer the subject fields.<br><br>/hitsmode my m3 770 620 10 1 0 1 250 1<br><br>770 is the distance from yer left hand margin.<br>620 is the distance from the top o' yer screen doonwards.<br>10 is the length (number o' lines) in the box.<br>1 is the font size.<br>0 is the header fer the box (0 fer none, 1 fer one)<br>1 is fer the backgroond (0 fer clear, 1 fer opaque)<br>250 is the width o' the window (appropiate fer long-winded names)<br>1 is fer permanency (0 tae disappear, 1 tae keep fixed)<br><br>I'd post a screenshot fer effect, but I dinnae think it's needed. And I havnae downloaded GIMP (Gnu Image Manipulation Program) since I refermatted a month ago, so I gots nothin' I kin edit the stinkin' .bmps wi' right now anyway. Been tae lazy. &lt;Chuckles&gt;<br><br>Glad it helped ye, Zeremus. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utostifenrirsget.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tosti Fenrirsget</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/23/02 11:36:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2056.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Them hitsmode are mostly fer high le'el folks.</span><hr size=1> Most folks accustomed tae spammy fights tern off their misses anyway. An' in yer higher le'els, if'n ye dual wield, ye MUST ha' a way o' filterin' yer damage from chat. Anya's Quickenin' will utterly destroy any communication - be it conversation or instructions via guildsay or elsewhere - guaranteed.<br><br>It's a wonderful addition, but ye're right, that flickerin' is awful annoyin' when ye opaque the backgroond. It happens whene'er somethin' new is scrolled in yer main chat window. They'll fix it soons, I'll bet. So I'm no' werried.<br><br>It's all aboot customisation. If ye dinnae like it, nae one ferces ye tae use them new hitsmodes. They're jes' utilities tae be used or discarded. The choice is a freedom unprecedented in EQ. I'm fiercely glad that they're no' all big dummies o'er there a'Verant Interactive. Goad knows Gordon is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2056.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2056.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=2056.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.threadControl?topicID=2056.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2056.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2056.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub42.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="ayonaerofrm1">General Forum<option value="ayonaerofrm6">NAG (Nearly Anything Goes)<option value="ayonaerofrm7">The Bazaar<option value="ayonaerofrm12">Nuggets<option value="ayon